ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC FASTKNN <options>;
    DISPLAY <table-list> </ options>;
    DISPLAYOUT table-spec-list </ options>;
    ID variables;
    INPUT variables;
    OUTPUT OUT=CAS-libref.data-table <options>;

The FASTKNN procedure implements the k-nearest neighbor (k-NN) search algorithm in SAS Viya. 
The k-NN algorithm has numerous applications, including recommendation systems, image search, 
fingerprint recognition, and clustering. You can use the FASTKNN procedure to read and write 
data in distributed form, and to perform search in parallel by making full use of multicore 
computers or distributed computing environments.

StatementHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: INPUT variables;

The INPUT statement specifies the variables to be used in the nearest neighbor search. 
The variables must be of interval type. You must specify at least one input variable.
